f=Engineering/axiom/operational/skill/axiom-skill-routing.md · p=axiom's four skills fit together. axiom department's algorithm-and-data-structure design layer: chooses structures, analyzes complexity, measures performance, reviews others' algorithmic code. designs advises; raj dana build choices. · h2:The shape=`dsa-design-records (which structure, and why — ADR for algorithms) \· ├─ complexity-analysis (the bounds it states: worst/avg/amortized, derived) \· └─ performance-profiling (the measurements when asymptotics don't settle it) \· │ \· algorithm-review (axiom's rigor applied to others' diffs — dev routing)` · h2:Routing rules="Which structure what algorithm this" **dsa-design-records**., "What's complexity scale O(n²)" **complexity-analysis**., "Optimize slow change faster profile" **performance-profiling** (measure first)., "Review algorithm correct" (usually dev routing) **algorithm-review**., Predict measure: complexity-analysis predicts, performance-profiling confirms; disagreement trust measurement. · h2:Handoffs=**dev**: dsa-design-records architecture-decisions' algorithm-layer child; system-wide choices escalate full ADR; algorithm-heavy diffs route algorithm-review (like security aegis)., **raj dana**: primary consumers hot-path structures (raj) storage/query structures (dana) get axiom's records review., **quinn**: complexity regressions algorithmic fragile areas feed gate regression map., **ops**: latency regressions monitoring route performance-profiling; benchmark numbers feed baselines., **cypher**: worst-case complexity triggers axiom identifies DoS surfaces (L10) cypher tests., Senior authority: **Security Charter** (axiom's tool use plan-locked/sandboxed); axiom runs data changes (Rail 3).